l","¼ tsp sea salt","130 g shelled unsalted pistachios","100 g rolled oats","20 g flaked almonds","4 slices fruit bread, thickly sliced","100 - 150 g goat's cheese","1 - 2 tbsp honey, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r82493","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZrU6epgCrd8\/XZafCkDjxoI\/AAAAAAAAgqk\/3VCay93g_agWnYNPiqQ2pWG3bJQhqn-DgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_gk_m-T-YOOgFWGyz.png","title":"Mixed fruit compote with goat's cheese and granola on toast","publishedAt":"2015-05-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"21 g","fat":"37 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"77.5 g","calories":"3098 kJ \/ 738 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sealable container, baking paper, deep-sided roasting tray (32 x 23 cm), toaster, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Serve leftover pistachio and oat granola on top of natural yoghurt and fresh fruit or as a base for homemade granola bars.","Try using a variety of seasonal fruits in the compote.","<strong>Rhubarb topping:<\/strong> Place 500g water into mixing bowl. Line Varoma dish with a piece of wet and well-wrung baking paper. Place Varoma into position and weigh 350 g rhubarb, cut into lengths (5 cm) on top of the baking paper. Drizzle with 20 g honey; ½ orange, zest only, no white pith; 2-3 cm piece ginger, peeled and grated; and 1-2 pinches cinnamon. Secure Varoma lid and steam <strong>13-15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong>, or until rhubarb is tender. Set rhubarb aside in a bowl, drizzle with an additional 20 g honey and allow to cool. Use the rhubarb topping in place of the mixed fruit compote."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","50m","4 portions"]}